## PART 2 — UPDATE GlobalStyle TYPE

In /lib/db/schema.ts and /lib/types.ts, update GlobalStyle:

```ts
export interface GlobalStyle {
  // Now just points to a preset + optional overrides
  presetId: StylePresetId

  // Optional per-project overrides (null = use preset default)
  paletteOverride: [string, string, string, string] | null
  bgColorOverride: string | null
  fontOverride: string | null

  // Deprecated individual fields — keep for migration only
  // New code reads from resolveStyle(presetId, overrides)
  palette?: [string, string, string, string]
  roughnessLevel?: number
  // etc — these become derived from preset
}
```

Migration: for existing projects that have the old flat GlobalStyle,
add a migration in /scripts/migrate-styles.ts that:
- Detects projects with old-style GlobalStyle (has palette but no presetId)
- Finds the closest matching preset by palette/bgColor similarity
- Sets presetId + moves any custom values to override fields
- Run once: npx tsx scripts/migrate-styles.ts

