## PART 4 — UPDATE AGENT SYSTEM PROMPTS

In /lib/agents/scene-maker.ts, inject style guidance
from the resolved preset into the system prompt:

```ts
function buildSceneMakerSystemPrompt(
  style: ResolvedStyle,
  activeTools: string[]
): string {
  return `You are the Scene Maker agent for Cench Studio.
Generate animated scenes that render in a browser and get captured by WVC.

## Active Style Preset: ${style.name} ${style.emoji}
${style.agentGuidance}

## Automatic style settings (DO NOT override these in generated code)
ROUGHNESS = ${style.roughnessLevel}
  — set automatically, rough.js applied based on this value
  — do not manually set roughness in tool calls

TOOL = '${style.defaultTool}'
  — default drawing tool is set by the style preset
  — only override for specific elements that need a different feel

STROKE_COLOR = '${style.strokeColor}'
  — primary stroke color for this style
  — use PALETTE[N] for accent colors

TEXTURE = ${style.textureStyle !== 'none' ? `'${style.textureStyle}' at ${Math.round(style.textureIntensity * 100)}% intensity` : 'none'}
  — applied automatically after rendering, do not add manually

PREFERRED RENDERER = ${style.preferredRenderer}
  — ${style.preferredRenderer === 'canvas2d'
       ? 'use canvas2d with animateRough* functions'
       : style.preferredRenderer === 'svg'
       ? 'use SVG with .stroke/.fadein CSS classes'
       : 'choose the best renderer per scene'}

## Core rules
${CORE_RULES}

## Available tools
${buildToolList(activeTools)}`;
}
```

