## PART 5 — UPDATE SKILL RULES

### Update .claude/skills/cench/rules/core.md

Add at the top, before all other rules:

```markdown
# Core Rules

## Style preset drives everything — read this first

The project has a style preset that automatically sets:
  ROUGHNESS     — how rough/wobbly strokes are (0=clean, 3=very rough)
  TOOL          — default drawing tool (marker, pen, chalk, etc)
  STROKE_COLOR  — the primary ink color for this style
  TEXTURE       — background texture (applied automatically)
  FONT          — default font family

These are injected as globals in every scene template.
DO NOT manually set roughness, tool, or texture in generated code.
Just use ROUGHNESS, TOOL, STROKE_COLOR as constants.

## Renderer preference

The style preset has a preferred renderer.
Check the system prompt for "PREFERRED RENDERER" before choosing
canvas2d vs svg for a scene.

Whiteboard/Chalkboard/Neon/Kraft → canvas2d (organic strokes)
Blueprint/Clean/Newspaper → svg (precise lines)
Data Story → auto (D3 for data, canvas2d for diagrams)

## Colors

Primary strokes: STROKE_COLOR (set by preset, may be white on dark bg)
Accent colors: PALETTE[1], PALETTE[2], PALETTE[3]
Never hardcode hex values.

## Everything else below applies regardless of style preset.
```

### Update .claude/skills/cench/rules/canvas2d.md

Remove the roughness guidance section — it's now automatic.
Replace with:

```markdown
## Roughness and tool — automatic from style preset

ROUGHNESS and TOOL are set automatically by the style preset.
Use them as constants — do not override unless you have a specific
reason for an individual element:

  // Normal usage — inherits preset roughness and tool
  await animateRoughLine(ctx, x1, y1, x2, y2, {
    color: STROKE_COLOR,
    seed: 1,
  }, 600);

  // Override for specific element (rare)
  await animateRoughLine(ctx, x1, y1, x2, y2, {
    color: PALETTE[1],
    roughness: 0,   // force clean line for this one element
    tool: 'pen',    // force pen for annotation
    seed: 2,
  }, 400);

Default opts when omitted:
  roughness: ROUGHNESS   (from preset)
  tool:      TOOL        (from preset)
  color:     STROKE_COLOR (from preset)
```

