## PART 7 — UPDATE CLAUDE.md

Add to the project CLAUDE.md so Claude Code understands
the automatic style system:

```markdown
## Style System

Projects use a style preset that automatically configures:
  - Renderer preference (canvas2d vs svg)
  - Roughness level (0-3)
  - Default drawing tool
  - Stroke color defaults
  - Background texture

When generating scenes, read the style guidance in the system prompt.
The globals ROUGHNESS, TOOL, STROKE_COLOR are injected automatically
by writeSceneHTML — do not hardcode these values in scene code.

Available presets: whiteboard, chalkboard, blueprint, clean,
data-story, newspaper, neon, kraft

Texture overlays are applied automatically after render —
do not add generateTextureCanvas() calls in scene code.
```

---

## IMPLEMENTATION ORDER

1. Create /lib/styles/presets.ts with all 8 preset definitions
2. Update GlobalStyle type to use presetId
3. Create /scripts/migrate-styles.ts and run it
4. Update renderCanvas2DTemplate() — inject preset globals,
   add automatic texture overlay code
5. Update renderSVGTemplate() — inject preset globals,
   add conditional Rough.js post-processing
6. Update buildBgStyleCSS() for grid/dots backgrounds
7. Update scene-maker agent system prompt to inject
   style.agentGuidance
8. Update core.md — add style preset section at top
9. Update canvas2d.md — replace roughness section
10. Build StylePresetPicker component
11. Replace GlobalStyle editor in Project Settings with picker
12. Test each preset end-to-end:
    - Set project to 'chalkboard'
    - Run /cench explain photosynthesis
    - Verify: dark bg, white strokes, chalk texture, high roughness
    - Set project to 'blueprint'
    - Run /cench explain TCP handshake
    - Verify: dark blue bg, grid, clean SVG lines, monospace font

---

## CRITICAL NOTES

The texture canvas sits on top of the main canvas using
CSS mix-blend-mode. This is why it works across all content
without knowing what's drawn — it's a post-process layer.

For chalkboard preset: strokeColorOverride is '#fffef9' (white).
The scene code should use STROKE_COLOR (not PALETTE[0]) as the
primary stroke color. PALETTE[0] is also white in this preset,
so it's the same value — but the distinction matters when users
override the palette while keeping the chalkboard preset.

For blueprint preset: roughnessLevel is 0. The Rough.js script
tag is conditionally excluded from the template when roughness=0,
keeping the scene HTML lean and avoiding unnecessary CDN loads.

hashString(scene.id) produces a deterministic seed for the
texture canvas based on the scene's UUID. This ensures the
same scene always renders the same texture pattern across
renders — critical for WVC export determinism.

The agentGuidance string in each preset is injected verbatim
into the scene-maker system prompt. Keep it concise — it adds
tokens to every generation call. Aim for 3-6 lines maximum.
```